      <prefercite id="aspace_3de9e6d0ab9d644f9b83cf701bcc7b77">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Andrew Jackson Davis Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_55634d44bfb62b7f09feff6ab7b6a319">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Andrew Jackson Davis: spiritualist; ran a "clairvoyant clinic" in Poughkeepsie; from 1845 on turned to writing and lecturing; practiced both mesmerism and spiritualism.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_85c762db6bf637f9b8734af19c3a11bf">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Letters from Andrew Jackson Davis, author and spiritualist to William Green, Jr., his benefactor. The letters deal with personal, family, and financial matters as well as Davis' work with spiritualism and healing.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
